    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13438#discussion_r3283868659\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why did this signature become fallible even though the function itself isn't fallible? This (along with the similar change to <code>get_gc_heap_bound</code>) seems to have added a whole bunch of noise to the diff.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 596835024,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779392571
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13438#pullrequestreview-4340249458\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 596839090,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779393902
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13438#discussion_r3283991948\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This was needed because the <code>func_environ.rs</code> file started calling this function, but it's only conditionally defined depending on the <code>gc</code> feature.</p>\n<p>Personally I'd like to actually remove the crate features of the <code>wasmtime-internal-cranelift</code> crate entirely since I don't think we benefit much from conditionally-compiled compiler code and it'd clean up the internals quite a bit (and be easier to mantain). I figured I'd defer that to a future PR though.</p>\n</blockquote>",
